<subSubSection id="66D86507FF82794FFF6147ADFA2FFDF5" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" type="key">
<keyStep id="95362E29FF82794FFF6147ADFA2EFED3" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<paragraph id="2E7D368CFF82794FFF6147ADFA2EFE95" blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead id="953395B9FF82794FFF6147ADFA2EFE95" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">1 Head black dorsally, except for yellowish median and lateral carinae; abdomen extensively black, usually on basal one half or more; femora smooth, at most, with only tiny, indistinct setigerous tubercles...................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E7D368CFF82794FFF614666FA2EFED3" blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead id="953395B9FF82794FFF614666FA2EFED3" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">- Head brown dorsally, sometimes dark brown or black along gular area; abdomen yellowish brown, often dark brown on basal third; femora with distinct setigerous tubercles, especially near apices............................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="95362E29FF82794FFF614623FA2FFE25" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<paragraph id="2E7D368CFF82794FFF614623FA2EFE1C" blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead id="953395B9FF82794FFF614623FA2EFE1C" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
2 Length of setae on antennal scape and femora short, subequal to or slightly greater than diameter of segments; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture nearly flat (
<figureCitation id="B6F92A09FF82794FFD73461EFD48FE1F" box="[645,762,367,389]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 24, 25</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="56D5761CFF82794FFC70461EFC54FE1F" box="[902,998,367,389]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Argentina</collectingCountry>
....................... 
<taxonomicName id="E9C24D0FFF82794FFB0B461FFA2EFE1C" authority="Stusak" authorityName="Stusak" authorityYear="1977" box="[1277,1436,366,390]" class="Insecta" family="Berytidae" genus="Metajalysus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis id="1CB6EA9EFF82794FFB0B461FFA2EFE1C" bold="true" box="[1277,1436,366,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<emphasis id="1CB6EA9EFF82794FFB0B461FFAE3FE1E" bold="true" box="[1277,1361,366,388]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">horvathi</emphasis>
Štusák
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E7D368CFF82794FFF6146FCFA2FFE25" blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead id="953395B9FF82794FFF6146FCFA2FFE25" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
- Length of setae on antennal scape and femora one and a half to two or more times diameter of segments; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture with sharp inverted V-shaped process (
<figureCitation id="B6F92A09FF82794FFCB646D8FC07FE5A" box="[832,949,425,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 28, 29</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="56D5761CFF82794FFBB446D8FB20FE25" box="[1090,1170,425,447]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
........... 
<emphasis id="1CB6EA9EFF82794FFAE346D8FA2FFE25" bold="true" box="[1301,1437,425,447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<taxonomicName id="E9C24D0FFF82794FFAE346D8FAE8FE25" authority="Henry &amp; Dellapé, 2021" authorityName="Henry &amp; Dellapé" authorityYear="2021" box="[1301,1370,425,447]" class="Insecta" family="Berytidae" genus="Metajalysus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="1CB6EA9EFF82794FFAE346D8FAE8FE25" bold="true" box="[1301,1370,425,447]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="078557E5FF82794FFA9046DBFA2FFE25" box="[1382,1437,426,447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="95362E29FF82794FFF6146B6FA2FFDF5" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<paragraph id="2E7D368CFF82794FFF6146B6FA2FFD8D" blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead id="953395B9FF82794FFF6146B6FA2FFD8D" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
3 Smaller species, length 
<quantity id="E93A9B69FF82794FFE3046B6FDE6FE46" box="[454,596,455,477]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.46" metricValueMax="3.62" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" unit="mm" value="3.46" valueMax="3.62" valueMin="3.3">3.30–3.62 mm</quantity>
; pronotum with ca. 12–15 or more erect setae on either side of disc (
<figureCitation id="B6F92A09FF82794FFB1F46B6FAF7FE47" box="[1257,1349,455,477]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Metajalysus spp. 1, M. clavatus, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 2, M. clavatus, male, lateral aspect. 3, M. clavatus, female, dorsal aspect. 4, M. graziae, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 5, M. graziae, male, lateral aspect. 6, M. graziae, female, dorsal aspect. Scale bar for plate = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692887/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
); femora clavate apically, yellowish brown with a distinct subapical dark brown band; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture with an inverted V-shaped process (
<figureCitation id="B6F92A09FF82794FFDCE4570FD1EFD82" box="[568,684,513,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="56D5761CFF82794FFCCF4570FC2BFD8D" box="[825,921,513,535]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.............................. 
<emphasis id="1CB6EA9EFF82794FFAFF4570FA2FFD8D" bold="true" box="[1289,1437,513,535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<taxonomicName id="E9C24D0FFF82794FFAFF4570FAE8FD8D" authority="Henry &amp; Dellapé, 2021" authorityName="Henry &amp; Dellapé" authorityYear="2021" box="[1289,1370,513,535]" class="Insecta" family="Berytidae" genus="Metajalysus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavatus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="1CB6EA9EFF82794FFAFF4570FAE8FD8D" bold="true" box="[1289,1370,513,535]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">clavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="078557E5FF82794FFA904573FA2FFD8D" box="[1382,1437,514,535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E7D368CFF82794FFF61456EFA2FFDF5" blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead id="953395B9FF82794FFF61456EFA2FFDF5" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
- Larger species, length 4.00- 
<quantity id="E93A9B69FF82794FFE1F456EFDF2FDAE" box="[489,576,543,565]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" unit="mm" value="4.68">4.68 mm</quantity>
, pronotum with ca. 5 or 6 erect setae on either side of disc (
<figureCitation id="B6F92A09FF82794FFB9B456EFB75FDAF" box="[1133,1223,543,565]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Metajalysus spp. 1, M. clavatus, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 2, M. clavatus, male, lateral aspect. 3, M. clavatus, female, dorsal aspect. 4, M. graziae, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 5, M. graziae, male, lateral aspect. 6, M. graziae, female, dorsal aspect. Scale bar for plate = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692887/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
); femora, more gradually enlarged to apex, yellowish brown to brown, with apex pale on darkest specimens; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture nearly straight across (
<figureCitation id="B6F92A09FF82794FFDE64528FD37FDEA" box="[528,645,601,624]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 21, 22</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="56D5761CFF82794FFCE64528FCC2FDF5" box="[784,880,601,623]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="56D5761CFF82794FFC694528FC54FDF5" box="[927,998,601,623]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
......................... 
